WEBVTT

00:00:03.060 --> 00:00:06.459
Shown here is the modern seaport of Joppa.

00:00:06.459 --> 00:00:12.460
It is located on the Mediterranean coast about halfway between Mount Carmel and Gaza.

00:00:12.460 --> 00:00:20.519
The modern city of Tel Aviv Yafo now occupies the site of the ancient city.

00:00:20.519 --> 00:00:26.920
It was to the ancient city of Joppa that the tyrians floated rafts of timber from the forests of Lebanon

00:00:26.920 --> 00:00:31.120
to be used in constructing Solomon's temple.

00:00:31.320 --> 00:00:39.320
Later, the prophet Jonah, seeking to flee his assignment, boarded a ship at Joppa bound for Tarshish.

00:00:39.320 --> 00:00:44.119
In the first century CE, a Christian congregation existed at Joppa.

00:00:44.119 --> 00:00:49.119
Among that group was Dorcas, Tabitha, whom Peter resurrected.

00:00:49.119 --> 00:00:58.119
And it was in Joppa while staying at Simon the Tanners house that Peter received the vision that prepared him to preach to the Gentile Cornelius.
